1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,930
Start your mental engine mechanically.

2
00:00:03,440 --> 00:00:08,769
An aspiring young writer who wasn't experiencing success made this confession.

3
00:00:09,200 --> 00:00:14,370
My trouble is, whole days and weeks pass that I can't get a thing written.

4
00:00:14,880 --> 00:00:18,130
You see, he remarked, writing is creative.

5
00:00:18,240 --> 00:00:19,890
You've got to be inspired.

6
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:21,970
Your spirit must move you.

7
00:00:22,720 --> 00:00:28,210
True, writing is creative, but here's how another creative man, also a writer,

8
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:33,490
explained his secret for producing quantities of successful material.

9
00:00:34,320 --> 00:00:37,650
I use a mind-force technique," he began.

10
00:00:37,920 --> 00:00:42,289
I've got deadlines to meet, and I can't wait for my spirit to move me.

11
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:44,370
I've got to move my spirit.

12
00:00:44,560 --> 00:00:46,210
Here's how my method works.

13
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:48,850
I make myself sit down at my desk.

14
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:53,170
Then I pick up a pencil and go through mechanical motions of writing.

15
00:00:53,279 --> 00:00:54,610
I put down anything.

16
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:55,809
I doodle.

17
00:00:55,920 --> 00:01:01,089
I get my fingers and arm in motion, and sooner or later, without my being conscious of it,

18
00:01:01,279 --> 00:01:03,650
my mind gets on the right track.

19
00:01:04,560 --> 00:01:09,250
Sometimes, of course, I get ideas out of the blue when I'm not trying to write,

20
00:01:09,250 --> 00:01:12,289
" he went on, but these are just bonuses.

21
00:01:12,720 --> 00:01:16,769
Most of the good ideas come from just getting to work.

22
00:01:17,519 --> 00:01:19,809
Action must precede action.

23
00:01:19,920 --> 00:01:21,410
That's a law of nature.

24
00:01:21,600 --> 00:01:27,250
Nothing starts itself, not even the dozens of mechanical gadgets we use daily.

25
00:01:28,160 --> 00:01:34,850
Your home is heated automatically, but you must select, take action, the temperature you want.

26
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:40,289
Your car shifts gears automatically only after you have set the right lever.

27
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:43,650
The same principle applies to mind action.

28
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:47,328
You get your mind in gear to make it produce for you.

29
00:01:48,480 --> 00:02:00,690
A young branch sales manager for a door-to-door sales organization explained how he trained his sales force the mechanical way to start each day earlier and more successfully.

30
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:08,450
There's a tremendous resistance to the door-to-door salesman, as anyone who has ever sold house-to-house knows,

31
00:02:08,480 --> 00:02:14,930
he commented, and it's hard, even for the veteran salesman, to make that first call in the morning.

32
00:02:15,279 --> 00:02:20,850
He knows the odds are pretty good that he'll get some pretty rough treatment before the day is over.

33
00:02:21,039 --> 00:02:24,930
So it's natural for him to put off getting started in the morning.

34
00:02:25,039 --> 00:02:28,465
He'll drink a couple of extra cups of coffee, maybe cruise around the neighborhood a while,
